This includes but is not limited to market research, assist with editing and writing, office duties, administrative assistance in any aspect of this multidimensional work and related efforts, including attending workshops, teaching classes and or workshops, recording/uploading information into different databases. 
Student must possess effective interpersonal, problem-solving, decision-making, and public relations, and business skills. 
Current or past business ownership preferred. 
18-20 hours per week. 
 
 Required Qualifications 
 Must be currently enrolled in Masters of Computer Science program at UVU Must be accepted into an MCS full-time or part-time program. 
 
 Knowledge, Skills and Abilities
 Know Python Coding Language Ability to review servers for malicious code Cybersecurity Understand Setting Up & Managing Server Racks CAD Design is a plus Understanding AI, Machine Learning, Neural Networks Computer skills in MS Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Mailchimp, Eventbrite, and Internet applications. Databases preferred Business skills including Marketing skills, financial statement analysis techniques, and principals Ability to communicate clearly and concisely both orally and in writing Ability to partner in various aspects of scholarly research Ability to work independently, multi-task, and follow projects through to completion Ability to learn new applications, databases and work closely with others Ability to perform administrative duties with minimal supervision Strong intellectual abilities Ability to pay particular attention to details Ability to teach effectively 
 
 Preferred Qualifications 
 
 Physical Requirements 
 Able to lift and carry tables, chairs, and other office equipment. 
 
